  <!-- Client Auth -->
  <p style="margin: 14px 0 10px;">
    <strong>CLIENT AUTHORIZATION SOURCE DOCUMENT MUST BE ATTACHED TO REQUEST.</strong>
  </p>

  <!-- BIC Section -->
  <p style="text-decoration: underline; margin-bottom: 5px;">Each Sender Authorization Process Type will require a BIC, DN or ID</p>
  <p style="margin-bottom: 6px;">
    <strong>BIC Address</strong> – The BIC address must be present on the Swift table, except for TRDS. Trade Authorization must be entered manually by the user.
  </p>

  <ul style="list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 30px; margin: 4px 0 16px;">
    <li style="margin-bottom: 3px;">COLC - Allow movement of cash (collateral) from segregated account to head account</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom: 3px;">COLS - Allow movement of shares (collateral) from segregated account to head account</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom: 3px;">DNPF - Do Not Allow MT304 Forward (AFWD) Processing</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom: 3px;">DNPA - Do Not Allow MT304 Spot (ASET) Processing</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom: 3px;">FWDP - Allow MT304 Forward (AFWD) Processing</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom: 3px;">
      PBAM - Payment Based Allocation Method<br>
      <span>CSG &amp; TAX must ensure Momentum profile is created for successful execution</span>
    </li>
    <li style="margin-bottom: 3px;">PMTS - Payment Authorization</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom: 3px;">TRDS - Trades Authorization Custody/ MX20022 Mutual Funds FTP</li>
  </ul>

  <!-- MX20022 -->
  <p style="margin-bottom: 12px;">
    <strong>MX20022 Mutual Fund Distinguished Name (DN)</strong><br>
    MFDN - Distinguished Names that are authorized to instruct trades for Mutual Funds MX20022 Messaging.
  </p>

  <!-- ACH -->
  <p style="margin-bottom: 12px;">
    <strong>ACH Identification Number (ID)</strong> - users must provide up to 18 characters.<br>
    ACHD – ACH Debit Blocking (ID) - Important: Removal of ACHD linkage from a blocked account to itself is strictly prohibited.
  </p>

  <!-- Timeframe -->
  <p style="color: #1f5c99; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline; margin-bottom: 5px;">Timeframe for Sender Authorization Updates</p>
  <p style="color: #1f5c99; line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 20px;">
    Sender Authorization updates occur in real time. If a current BIC/ACH ID/DN is being removed, the client must not continue to submit instructions under that BIC/ACH ID/DN, as doing so will result in a failed transaction. If the client submits an instruction using the previous BIC/ACH ID/DN and the transaction fails, CSG must coordinate with Trade Management, Funds Transfer, and Mutual Fund Dept to repair the failed client transaction.
  </p>

